  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nFork choice looks at the epoch boundary block (`attestation.data.target.root`) rather than the most recent Beacon block when determining the head (`attestation.data.beacon_block_root`), here: https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/bbde06eb9f2b7a5ae00a3c6f41295bb8f1fcd083/beacon_node/beacon_chain/src/fork_choice.rs#L135\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nWe should change fork choice to use the `beacon_block_root` of the attestation instead, as per the spec: https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/v0.8.1/specs/core/0_fork-choice.md#on_attestation\r\n",
